		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Well, I did some investigation and uncovered a mistake on my part.  First, I thought I was at the skill level of 198 in Jewelry, I was not, I was at 196 (and still am).  I have been working on this Fire Opal option to see how it worked.  So I got a boatload of money and headed up to the Temple, then proceeded to buy individual Fire Opals at 55pp each. <br>  <br> First, this was a very tedious process as I had to use MANY mouse clicks to get to 55pp.  Second, you get some experience, but very little, I saw no change in my bar after purchasing 50 of these Fire Opals.  Third, you get a faction increase in Temple of Solusek Ro and a faction decrease in Shadowmen. <br>  <br> Now that I have worn my fingers to a bone, I started crafting gold fire opal wedding rings.  Unfortunately, they were trivial for me at 196 :-(  So all this work was nearly for naught.  There wasn't anyplace handy to sell the finished product which also put a cramp in my style. <br>  <br> Personally, after having tried this, I don't think I would use the Fire Opal to try to increase my skill.  It is too inconvenient and for the massive numbers of attempts required to get a single skill increase (on average), I would have my fingers in a cast. <br>  <br> I suspect that before Fire Emeralds, you can do Fire Opals, but they trivial at 196 or before, I would guess. <br>  <br> Well, more information to be passed around.  I would be interested in hearing other's experiences. <br>  <br> Galdilor Oretur <br> Enchanter of 22 Seasons, Prexus <br> Master Jeweler (196)		

